summary: I don’t think people realize just how weird Caleb’s sense of boundaries is.  Because it’s not just the ‘do-not-touch,’...
body: I don’t think people realize just how weird Caleb’s sense of boundaries is.  Because it’s not just the ‘do-not-touch,’ uncomfortable with physical contact, doesn’t know how to hug somebody thing.  There’s all of that - and then there’s the places where he doesn’t seem to have any fucking boundaries at all.  Like, he was totally fine just getting his dick out in the middle of a sewer in front of all his friends and also an enemy assassin because he thought it was the best way to make a point.  idk, maybe it’s related to spending most of his adult life in an institution?  but his idea of boundaries that aren’t about actual physical touching is real weird.

summary: Dungeons & Dragons Discourse Community Survey
title: Dungeons & Dragons Discourse Community Survey
excerpt: This survey of the Dungeons & Dragons community is being conducted by Kiran A. for WRIT 1133 at University of Denver. Responses will be used as primary research in an essay regarding this specific discourse community.
description: hi guys!! i’m in a research writing class at my uni and we’re doing papers regarding discourse communities, which basically means we’re studying a specific social group from a certain angle that may be unexplored thus far, in order to learn more about what defines that certain community. my paper is on dungeons & dragons, and so i have a survey about it! you don’t have to have ever played d&d before to take it; there’s a portion for non-players regarding their outsider perceptions of the game. it’d be super helpful if you could take this survey and send it to anyone you know who might want to take it (especially if they do play d&d!)! thank you!!
